The Mott–Schottky plot was obtained from IMPE-Impedance-Potential measurements using a CHI 760 potentiostat with a m-TiO2|FTO electrode (three-electrode configuration). Potential range was 0.5–1.4 V vs. RHE in 1 M KOH (pH 13.9). The frequency was set to 1000 Hz and the amplitude to 0.01 V. Epoxy resin was used to cover any exposed FTO, leaving only the TiO2 exposed. The donor density, ND, was calculated from the slopes of the Mott–Schottky plot, using Eq. (1)3511C2=2eεε0NDE−Efb−kTe\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
